---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout 
  title="Size Guide | Yilong Medical Scrubs" 
  description="Complete size chart for Yilong medical scrubs. XS to 6XL, US/UK/AU conversions. How to measure chest, waist, and hip. Plus size availability."
  keywords="scrubs size guide, medical uniform size chart, hospital uniform sizing, nursing scrubs sizes"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <div class="inline-block px-4 py-1 bg-secondary/20 border border-secondary/30 text-secondary text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest rounded-full mb-4">Reference Guide</div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-black mb-4">Size Guide</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-300 max-w-xl mx-auto">Yilong scrubs are sized to US industry standards. Most styles available from XXS to 6XL.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Size Table -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black mb-2 text-slate-900">Complete Size Chart</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-8">All measurements in centimeters (cm). For inch conversions, divide cm by 2.54.</p>
        
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm md:text-base border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-slate-900 text-white">
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold">US Size</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold">Yilong Size</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold">Chest (cm)</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold">Waist (cm)</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold">Hip (cm)</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold">UK / AU</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-200">
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary">XXS</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">XXS</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">88</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">78</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">92</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">0–2</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary">XS</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">XS</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">92</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">82</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">96</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">4–6</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary">S</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">S</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">98</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">88</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">102</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">8–10</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary">M</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">M</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">104</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">94</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">108</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">12–14</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary">L</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">L</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">110</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">100</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">114</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">16–18</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary">XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">116</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">106</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">120</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">20–22</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary">2XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">2XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">122</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">112</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">126</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">24–26</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary">3XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">3XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">128</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">118</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">132</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">28–30</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary bg-slate-100">4XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">4XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">134</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">124</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">138</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">—</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary bg-slate-100">5XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">5XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">140</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">130</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">144</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">—</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-bold text-secondary bg-slate-100">6XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">6XL</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">146</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">136</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">150</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 bg-slate-100">—</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-3">* Plus sizes (4XL–6XL) available for most styles. MOQ applies. Contact us for plus size availability.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Measurement Guide -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-20 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black mb-8 text-slate-900">How to Measure</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-slate-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-secondary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-black text-sm flex-shrink-0">1</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-black text-lg mb-2 text-slate-900">Chest / Bust</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Wrap a soft tape measure around the fullest part of your chest, keeping the tape horizontal and about 2cm below your armpits. Keep the tape snug but not tight. This is the most important measurement for scrubs tops.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-slate-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-secondary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-black text-sm flex-shrink-0">2</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-black text-lg mb-2 text-slate-900">Waist</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Measure around the narrowest part of your natural waistline. This is usually about 2–3 cm above your belly button. For jogger-style scrubs pants, this measurement is critical for the right fit.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-slate-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-secondary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-black text-sm flex-shrink-0">3</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-black text-lg mb-2 text-slate-900">Hip</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Measure around the fullest part of your hips and buttocks, keeping the tape horizontal. Usually about 20–22 cm below your waist. Important for scrub pants that need to fit over hips.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Market Tips -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-20 bg-white border-t border-slate-100">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black mb-8 text-slate-900">Size Preferences by Market</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-3">🇺🇸 USA / Canada</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Typical range: XS – 3XL. US sizing runs slightly larger than international. When in doubt between two sizes, size up for comfort in healthcare environments.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-3">🇬🇧 UK / 🇦🇺 Australia</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Typical range: 4–26 (UK). Generally runs 1–2 sizes smaller than US. Consider ordering up one UK size from your usual.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-3">🇪🇺 Europe</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Typical range: S – 3XL. European sizing tends to be more fitted. Consider going one size up for a relaxed fit typical in healthcare settings.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 mb-3">🌏 Asia / Middle East</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Typical range: XS – 2XL. Asian markets often prefer a more fitted cut. Provide your actual body measurements for the best fit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Size Exchange -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-20 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-secondary/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
          <span class="text-3xl">↔️</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black mb-4 text-slate-900">What If the Size Doesn't Fit?</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed">We want you to get the right fit the first time. If a size doesn't work out, here is our policy:</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-left">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2 text-sm">Free Exchange</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs leading-relaxed">Exchange for a different size. Buyer pays return shipping. Contact us within 7 days of receipt.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2 text-sm">Next Order Credit</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs leading-relaxed">Receive credit toward your next order for any sizing issue. No return needed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2 text-sm">Custom Sizing</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs leading-relaxed">For bulk orders (200+), we can adjust the size chart to your market specifications.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-16 bg-secondary text-white text-center">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-black mb-4">Not Sure Which Size to Order?</h2>
      <p class="text-emerald-100 max-w-lg mx-auto mb-6">Send us your body measurements and target market — we will recommend the right size for you.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-white text-secondary font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full hover:bg-slate-100 transition shadow-lg">Ask for Size Advice</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
